7. The privacy rights of California residents
This is a separate privacy statement for California users to comply with the California Consumer Privacy Act of 2018 (“CCPA”) and other California privacy laws. This statement is intended to supplement the information described in our \<Privacy Policy> and only applies to users who live in California (“consumers” or “you” or “users”).
This policy only applies to California users. If you are not a California resident, this policy does not apply to you. Please refer to our main privacy statement.
7.1. Your right to request information
According to the requirements of CCPA, you (or your authorized agent) have the right to request that we disclose to you information on how we have collected, used and shared your personal information in the past 12 months. This information includes: our set of personal information categories; the categories of the sources of personal information we collect; the business purposes for which we collect the personal information; and the categories of third parties with which we share personal information.
7.2. Your right to delete information
According to CCPA, you (or your authorized agent) have the right to choose not to sell or share your information. You (or your agent) have the right to ask us to delete your specific personal information that we have collected and kept from you, except in the following cases. Such cases include:
We need your information to detect security incidents and prevent malicious or illegal activities;
We need your information to identify and repair application errors that damage existing expected functions; we need your information to exercise freedom of speech, ensure that other consumers exercise the right to freedom of speech, or exercise other rights stipulated by law.
Based on your relationship with us, we need your information for internal use that is reasonably consistent with your expectations; and other circumstances required by CCPA and other California laws.
7.3. How do you exercise your rights
To exercise the above rights, please submit a verifiable user request to us via
support@liuzhosoft.com
Only you or your authorized agent can make verifiable consumer requests for your personal information. You can only request verifiable consumer information twice in a 12-month period. A verifiable consumer request must: Provide sufficient information to enable us to reasonably verify your identity and to confirm that we have collected personal information about you. Describe your request in sufficient detail so that we can understand and respond to it.
If we are unable to verify your identity, we will not be able to accurately respond to your request.
7.4. How do we respond to your request
We strive to respond to verifiable consumer requests within 45 days of receipt. If we need more time (up to 90 days), we will notify you of the reason and extension by email, phone or other electronic means.
We will not charge a fee for processing or responding to your verifiable consumer request unless the request is excessive, repetitive, or clearly unfounded. If we determine that the request requires payment, we will tell you why we made the decision, and provide you with a cost estimate before completing your request, and ensure that all of this is within the scope of the law.
7.5. non-discrimination
We will not discriminate against you for exercising any of your CCPA rights. Such discrimination includes: refusing to provide you with our services; charging you different prices or rates for our services; providing you with different levels or quality of our services; implying that you may receive different service prices or Rates, or services of different levels or quality.
7.6. Instructions for collecting data on minors
These services are not for anyone under 13 years of age. We do not knowingly collect personally identifiable information from children under 13 years of age. If we find that a child under the age of 13 has provided us with personal information, we will immediately delete this information from our servers. If you are a parent or guardian and you know that your child has provided us with personal information, please contact us so that we can take the necessary action. For users aged 13-16, they have the right to choose to join. If you are the parent or guardian of users aged 13-16, you can also contact us.
8. Data protection
We are fully aware of the importance of personal data, and we will do our best to protect your data, but please understand that no means can be foolproof, and we cannot guarantee the safety of these data. We recommend that you carefully disclose data to the outside world and ensure that you do your best to protect the security of your data.
9. Children’s privacy
These services are not for anyone under 13 years of age. We do not knowingly collect personally identifiable information from children under 13 years of age. If we find that a child under the age of 13 has provided us with personal information, we will immediately delete this information from our servers. If you are a parent or guardian and you know that your child has provided us with personal information, please contact us so that we can take the necessary action.
10. Policy changes
Any information collected is subject to the policies in effect at the time such information was collected. However, we may modify the policy from time to time. If such changes are made, we will provide you with other forms of modification or update notifications according to the situation. Your continued use of our applications or services after the policy changes will mean that you accept these changes, and the policy update date will be attached to the head of this clause.
11. Contact us
If you have any questions or concerns about this policy, you can contact us by
email:
support@liuzhosoft.com
